article.headline: Cal Poly 61, UC Irvine 58
article.story: IRVINE, Calif. (AP) -- Trae Clark scored 15 including the game's last four points as Cal Poly San Luis Obispo stunned UC Irvine 61-58 Saturday, dropping the Anteaters out of first place in the Big West Conference. Trailing 58-57 with 51.5 seconds to play, Clark dribbled down the right side of the court and sank an eight-foot bank shot over two UC Irvine players, giving the Mustangs (7-14, 5-4) a 59-58 lead with 40 seconds to play. UC Irvine (13-11, 9-3) had a chance to take the lead, but Gabe Stephenson blocked Aaron Fitzgerald's shot, and Clark controlled the rebound before being fouled by Adam Metelski. Clark made both free throws to complete the scoring and put Pacific percentage points ahead in the conference race. Pacific is 8-2 (.800), Irvine 9-3 (.750). Derek Stockalper scored 11 points for the Mustangs, and Dawin Whiten scored 10. Shamar Armstrong led all scorers with a career-high 16 points, making his first five field-goal attempts before missing two of his last three.
